{
  "text": "These data support our hypothesis [CITATION_1] ) that differences in developmental rate between homozygotes and heterozygotes may account for the positive association between developmental stability and heterozygosity reported by . We have observed that the magnitude of association between heterozygosity and hatching time differs between strains of rainbow trout and enzyme loci. In many cases, those strains and loci that showed significant associations between heterozygosity and developmental rate also showed associations between heterozygosity and developmental stability [CITATION_2] . For example, there is a significant negative correlation between developmental time and heterozygosity in the Arlee strain [CITATION_3] . This strain also showed a significant positive association between heterozygosity and developmental stability in two separate generations [CITATION_4] .",
